.TH BW-ENCODE 1 "January 2026" "Bitwarden CLI" "User Commands"

.SH NAME
bw-encode \- base64 encode stdin for use with create and edit commands

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bw encode

.SH DESCRIPTION
Encode input from stdin to base64 format. This is required when creating
or editing objects in the vault, as the CLI expects JSON data to be
base64-encoded.

This command is typically used in a pipeline with \fBbw create\fP or
\fBbw edit\fP commands.

.SH OPTIONS
This command has no specific options. It reads from stdin and writes
base64-encoded output to stdout.

.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Encode JSON for creating an item:
.nf
$ echo '{"name":"Test","type":2}' | bw encode
eyJuYW1lIjoiVGVzdCIsInR5cGUiOjJ9
.fi
.TP
Typical workflow for creating items:
.nf
$ bw get template item.login | jq '.name="My Login"' | bw encode | bw create item
.fi
.TP
Encode a file:
.nf
$ cat item.json | bw encode
.fi
.TP
Encode with manual input:
.nf
$ bw encode << EOF
{"name": "Test Folder"}
EOF
.fi

.SH NOTES
.TP
\(bu
Does not require authentication.
.TP
\(bu
Input should be valid JSON for create/edit operations.
.TP
\(bu
Output is standard base64 encoding.
.TP
\(bu
Use \fBjq\fP or similar tools to construct JSON before encoding.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Encoding completed successfully.
.TP
.B 1
Error occurred.

